\begin_layout Section
TIME-AWARE FRAME LENGTH FOR ISO 18000-6C PROTOCOL
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this section a description of the slot durations in the ISO 18000-6C
 standard is summarized, which is the most widely used standard for commercial
 RFID systems.
 Referring to the ISO 18000-C6 protocol 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "standard"

\end_inset

, figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Slot-Durations-During"

\end_inset

 shows the different types of slots.
 Each slot contains different sequences of reader to tag commands and tag
 replies.
 The duration of each slot is described in the following part:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Successful slot: In a successful slot the reader begins with query command,
 asking the tags to choose one slot from the frame and wait time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{1}$
\end_inset

 until receiving reply.
 In this slot the reader receives a single reply containing 16 bits random
 number called (RN16).
 As soon as the reader could recognize this RN16, which takes time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{2}$
\end_inset

, the reader replies with an acknowledgment command, asking the tag for
 its EPC code and waits again for time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 Finally, after receiving the EPC code from the tag, the reader starts a
 new slot after time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{2}.$
\end_inset

 Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:ts description"

\end_inset

 clarifies the time duration equation for successful slots.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{footnotesize}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
t_{s}=T_{q}+2\, T_{1}+T_{RN16}+2T_{2}+T_{Ack}+T_{EPC}\label{eq:ts description}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{footnotesize}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

