\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Collided slot: In a collided slot, the reader also starts with a query command
 asking the tags for a reply.
 The reader waits for time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{1}$
\end_inset

 until it receives replies from the tags.
 However in this slot, more than one tag replies by their RN16.
 Due to the resulting collisions the reader is not able identify any of
 these tags, so it directly starts a new slot after time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:tc description"

\end_inset

 states the time duration equation for collided slots: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{footnotesize}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
t_{c}=T_{q}+T_{1}+T_{RN16}+T_{2}\label{eq:tc description}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{footnotesize}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Idle slot: In this slot, also the reader sends a query command to the tags,
 and waits for time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 However, the reader receives no reply from the tags, then the reader terminates
 the slot and begins a new slot after time 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{3}$
\end_inset

.
 Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:te description"

\end_inset

 describes the time duration equation for idle slots:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{footnotesize}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
t_{e}=T_{q}+T_{1}+T_{3}\label{eq:te description}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{footnotesize}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
According to equations 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:ts description"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:tc description"

\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:te description"

\end_inset

, and based on the EPC standard values in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:ISO-18000-6C-TIMING"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{s}=3606.5\,\mu s$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{c}=850\,\mu s$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{e}=175\,\mu s$
\end_inset

, which lead us to the constant 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{t}=0.2$
\end_inset

.
 According to equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Lopt aprox"

\end_inset

, the real optimum frame length should be 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{opt}=1.9\, n$
\end_inset

, which is almost double the value of the conventional optimum frame length.
\end_layout

